name: .JHTML File Extension
summary: Learn about .JHTML files and view a list of programs that open them.

description: HTML file that includes Java code; similar to a standard .HTML file, but may include Java functions that are processed on the server before the page is sent to the client's Web browser; can also access information from a database using a JDBC (Java Database Connectivity) connection.

content: JHTML files may be created using the ATG (Art Technology Group) Dynamo Document Editor and may be parsed on a Web server with the Dynamo Application Server installed. Dynamo is now part of the ATG Commerce software package.
